

Compile 

Linux runtime need libasound-devel make gcc CMake packages

The following command :

cd AVDSP/module_avdsp
mkdir build
cd build
cmake ..
make 

will create the dspcreate binary and the libasound_module_pcm_avdsp.so alsa external pluging  in the build directory


Install

Copy the libasound_module_pcm_avdsp.so into your distrib  alsa external plugin directory .
For fedora , it's : /usr/lib64/alsa-lib/

Create an alasa device in your alsa conf file (.asoundrc /etc/asound.conf etc ...) :
pcm.dsp {
        type avdsp
	dspprog "/mydir/myavdsp.bin"
	dither 23
        slave {
                pcm "hw:x20,0"
        }
}


